message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - This paper presents a method for automated pancreas segmentation from CT volumes using deep learning techniques. The paper utilizes 3D fully convolutional network (FCN) feature-based pancreas localization and regression forests for segmentation. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, since the paper focuses on medical image analysis, it could also belong to the medical imaging (cs.MED) and neuroscience (cs.NEURON) sub-categories.
